1
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:19,960
BOONYAVEJ HOSPITAL

2
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:23,000
- There are two issues, sir.
- Yes.

3
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:26,360
First, the wound on his hand.
I've treated it already.

4
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:29,320
- Yes.
- And second, the fever.

5
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:31,200
The fever?

6
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:34,040
Would the patient be comfortable
being admitted for two nights?

7
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:37,600
That's fine. I'll leave it to you, Doctor.
Whatever you think is best.

8
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:39,040
I'll take care of him from here.

9
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:42,400
Then go on, hurry.
Don't worry. You'll be late.

10
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:43,480
Go on. Hurry.

11
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:10,400
<i>If you don't feel guilty,</i>
<i>then don't bother apologizing.</i>

12
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:38,480
Hello.

13
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:40,720
What's wrong?

14
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:43,120
You fought with Det again, didn't you?

15
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:45,000
<i>How did you know?</i>

16
00:04:45,520 --> 00:04:46,880
Hey, Na,

17
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:49,720
every time you fight with Det,
you call me right away.

18
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:52,720
I feel strange.

19
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:55,200
Strange? How?

20
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:56,840
I think I might be pregnant.

21
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:58,240
Pregnant by Det?

22
00:04:58,320 --> 00:04:59,720
Yeah, maybe.

23
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:03,400
Na, what do you mean maybe?

24
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:04,840
It's Det.

25
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:06,880
If not him, then who else would it be?

26
00:05:06,960 --> 00:05:08,360
Oh, Na.

27
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:09,880
Talk to you later.

28
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,120
Det.

29
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:29,240
We need to talk.

30
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,960
Mr. Jirasin,
how much longer will you take?

31
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:43,040
About ten or fifteen minutes.
I'm almost there.

32
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:46,160
There was a small problem at home.

33
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:49,280
Uncle Rut had an accident,

34
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:51,120
so I had to take him to the hospital.

35
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:52,480
Um, that's fine.

36
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:55,240
Since it's urgent, I'll inform Mrs. Wanee.

37
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:56,840
Alright, thank you.

38
00:05:58,120 --> 00:06:01,760
Just a moment.
It shouldn't be more than ten minutes.

39
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:07,120
Hello.

40
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:08,920
<i>Yes, Mr. Sin.</i>

41
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:10,480
Everything is going according to plan.

42
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:12,920
Prepare our people.

43
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:24,760
Hey.

44
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:28,600
Are you okay?

45
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:37,080
They've broken into Baan Saeng.

46
00:06:42,080 --> 00:06:43,400
Do you need more people?

47
00:06:45,080 --> 00:06:47,640
I think the most important thing
right now is Ms. Kluay.

48
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:49,840
I know now.

49
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:52,600
I'm not…

50
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:55,080
Madam requests
your presence downstairs, Mr. Warat.

51
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:22,600
Det.

52
00:07:28,440 --> 00:07:30,520
You're going to be a father.

53
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:35,040
What do you mean?

54
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:39,320
What do I mean? Well,

55
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:40,600
I just told you

56
00:07:41,640 --> 00:07:45,000
you're going to be a father.

57
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:48,480
Did you forget

58
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:51,280
what you did yesterday?

59
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:56,000
Yesterday…

60
00:07:57,960 --> 00:07:59,280
You disappeared with Warat.

61
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,400
You made me feel

62
00:08:02,280 --> 00:08:03,400
like I'm nothing but trash.

63
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:05,880
Det…

64
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:08,640
I'm just some lowly person,

65
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:11,360
not someone high-class like you.

66
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:13,320
You're the one

67
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:16,160
who lowered yourself to be with me.

68
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:21,800
What's…

69
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,320
What's in the past…

70
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:27,280
just forget it, Det.

71
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:29,280
Please.

72
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:33,200
No, I can't forget it.

73
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:38,799
I'm just a servant's son.

74
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:42,520
I'm not worthy of someone like you.

75
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:46,480
You're the one
who belongs up there. And that

76
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:48,760
will always be the truth.

77
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:52,600
The one who truly suits you

78
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:56,280
is Warat, not me.

79
00:08:57,560 --> 00:08:58,600
Det…

80
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:02,280
I'm sorry.

81
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:05,520
Let's…

82
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:09,400
Let's start over, okay?

83
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:13,280
And the baby in your womb,

84
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:15,800
are you sure…

85
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:19,080
it's mine?

86
00:09:26,680 --> 00:09:28,400
Det, what are you saying?

87
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:34,320
You've looked down on me all this time.

88
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:37,440
I endured it, I put up with it.

89
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:39,800
But today…

90
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:44,960
I said I'm sorry, Det.

91
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:47,480
Can you stay with me?

92
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:50,240
You think saying sorry
will fix everything?

93
00:09:51,560 --> 00:09:52,920
The truth won't change.

94
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:55,080
You've always thought

95
00:09:55,880 --> 00:09:58,000
my father was just your father's servant.

96
00:09:59,520 --> 00:10:00,520
Det,

97
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:04,720
I love you.

98
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:08,160
Don't say that word.

99
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:11,080
The child in your womb…

100
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:13,080
Don't say it.

101
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:15,080
It's not my child.

102
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:26,920
- Det.
- Let's break up, Ameena.

103
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:28,920
No.

104
00:10:29,440 --> 00:10:32,000
Det, don't go.

105
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:33,560
I already said it.

106
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:36,240
Let's break up.

107
00:10:36,760 --> 00:10:38,640
Det…

108
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:17,200
Right now, we're only missing Mr. Jirasin.

109
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:19,720
Why do we have to wait for him?

110
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:22,280
There's been a minor accident.

111
00:11:22,360 --> 00:11:24,480
Sin had an accident?

112
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:26,360
It's Mr. Sarut.

113
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:30,560
Huh? Is it serious?

114
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:33,320
Mr. Jirasin didn't say,

115
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:35,840
but he said
he had to take him to the hospital.

116
00:11:42,560 --> 00:11:43,600
Everyone,

117
00:11:47,880 --> 00:11:49,680
before we discuss the will,

118
00:11:51,160 --> 00:11:52,840
I have something important to tell you.

119
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:55,720
Let's talk about it later.

120
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:57,200
Grandma,

121
00:11:58,200 --> 00:11:59,560
it's really important.

122
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:04,880
I…

123
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:43,280
Dad.

124
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:46,760
Today, the Vanich family
is opening the will.

125
00:12:47,360 --> 00:12:48,520
Yes.

126
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:52,040
And the one who will lead the family next

127
00:12:52,120 --> 00:12:53,480
is Warat.

128
00:12:54,560 --> 00:12:55,600
If you

129
00:12:56,120 --> 00:12:57,480
can get Warat under your control,

130
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:00,120
you'll control Vanich Mall.

131
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:05,680
I'm pregnant, Dad.

132
00:13:07,920 --> 00:13:08,760
What did you say?

133
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:10,480
I'm pregnant.

134
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:12,400
Pregnant? With whose child?

135
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:14,680
- Don't tell me it's--
- Det's.

136
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:18,160
I shouldn't have let you stay with Det

137
00:13:18,680 --> 00:13:20,520
at such a crucial time.

138
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:24,520
- Where is he now?
- He's gone.

139
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:26,160
Gone?

140
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:28,680
Where did he go?

141
00:13:29,400 --> 00:13:31,080
He broke up with me.

142
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:33,400
Det, that bastard.

143
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:35,680
When he found out I was pregnant,

144
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:38,440
he asked

145
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:42,520
how I could be sure the baby was his.

146
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:44,520
Does anyone else know about this?

147
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:46,640
I've only told Det

148
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:48,560
and one friend.

149
00:13:50,080 --> 00:13:50,920
Good.

150
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:53,600
You're pregnant with Warat's child.

151
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,040
What?

152
00:13:57,120 --> 00:13:58,880
Go and make sure Warat is in your grasp.

153
00:13:59,720 --> 00:14:02,720
If you tell him you're carrying his child,
he won't dare abandon you.

154
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:03,720
But…

155
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:05,920
Det is just a servant's son.

156
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:08,080
Don't get so hung up on him.

157
00:14:08,680 --> 00:14:11,960
But one day, everyone will know the truth.

158
00:14:12,040 --> 00:14:14,040
By the time that day comes,

159
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:17,640
you'll have already taken
almost all of Vanich's assets.

160
00:14:20,880 --> 00:14:22,880
Do as I told you.

161
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:25,280
I'll deal with Wanee myself.

162
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:50,800
Uh… I'm sorry I'm late.

163
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:53,280
Shall we start?

164
00:14:53,360 --> 00:14:54,800
I'm sorry.

165
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:58,120
Can I speak with my grandmother alone?

166
00:14:58,640 --> 00:15:00,240
I think you should calm down first.

167
00:15:00,880 --> 00:15:02,960
Mr. Arnon, I've thought this through.

168
00:15:03,040 --> 00:15:04,040
Rat.

169
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:07,440
Can we at least wait
until the will is announced first?

170
00:15:07,520 --> 00:15:09,280
- Then we can talk after that.
- No.

171
00:15:10,760 --> 00:15:11,520
I have to say it now.

172
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:14,320
Warat, everyone here already knows

173
00:15:14,400 --> 00:15:17,960
that you're getting Vanich Mall
to manage because of Grandma.

174
00:15:18,040 --> 00:15:19,960
What more do you want?

175
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:22,360
People should know when enough is enough.

176
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:27,760
- It's not like that.
- Then what is it like?

177
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:30,520
Are you trying to
take everything for yourself?

178
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:34,400
You think Grandma loves you
so you can do whatever you want?

179
00:15:34,480 --> 00:15:37,280
Maybe we should give Mr. Warat some time.

180
00:15:37,960 --> 00:15:39,720
Mr. Warat, do you have something to say?

181
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:43,600
No. I just want to speak
with my grandmother alone.

182
00:15:44,640 --> 00:15:45,480
Uh…

183
00:15:45,560 --> 00:15:48,160
Ma'am, perhaps you should rest first.

184
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:49,400
No, it's fine.

185
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:52,800
We've come this far.
What secrets could there still be?

186
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:55,720
Whatever it is, just say it.

187
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:58,960
- I think…
- Yes, say everything.

188
00:15:59,040 --> 00:16:00,520
It's not what you think.

189
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:03,080
And how do you know what I'm thinking?

190
00:16:03,160 --> 00:16:04,960
You've already gotten
almost everything, Warat.

191
00:16:05,040 --> 00:16:07,000
Alright, that's enough.

192
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:09,440
- I want to give up…
- Stop.

193
00:16:10,720 --> 00:16:12,880
Don't say another word.

194
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:16,560
Warat, come with me.

195
00:16:43,680 --> 00:16:45,400
Really, Arnon?

196
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:47,560
<i>Mr. Warat went in to talk with Mrs. Wanee.</i>

197
00:16:47,640 --> 00:16:49,320
What's wrong with him?

198
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:52,960
Why would he ruin things like that?
That's not like him at all.

199
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:57,080
Oh, Mom's back. I'll talk to you later.

200
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:01,280
- You're back?
- Yes.

201
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:08,440
Were you talking to Mr. Arnon?

202
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:11,200
Yes. How was your meeting?

203
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:12,920
Good news.

204
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:17,520
Our partner network has agreed
to let Vanich Mall do CSR with us.

205
00:17:17,599 --> 00:17:20,079
Oh. That's great.

206
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:22,240
So the trip wasn't for nothing.

207
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:26,880
Mm. Where's Kluay today?

208
00:17:28,880 --> 00:17:32,160
There was a bit of an issue
at the Vanich house today.

209
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:34,760
Mr. Warat…

210
00:17:35,560 --> 00:17:39,280
Well, that's why Mrs. Wanee
just walked out of the room.

211
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:41,360
What happened?

212
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:43,600
And what did Kluay say?

213
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:45,440
- Kluay?
- Yes.

214
00:17:45,520 --> 00:17:48,240
Som, Mr. Warat is acting really strange.

215
00:17:48,320 --> 00:17:49,680
<i>Why?</i>

216
00:17:49,760 --> 00:17:52,040
I don't know.

217
00:17:52,120 --> 00:17:56,320
Whenever something happens,
we always talk it out.

218
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:58,200
- But…
- But what?

219
00:17:58,280 --> 00:18:01,600
I don't know. Right now I feel like
I'm being left out.

220
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:04,680
You're overthinking. It's nothing.

221
00:18:04,760 --> 00:18:07,360
It's like

222
00:18:07,440 --> 00:18:11,080
whenever he has something on his mind,
he doesn't want to talk to me anymore.

223
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:14,880
If he doesn't want me
involved in his personal matters,

224
00:18:15,440 --> 00:18:17,040
should I…?

225
00:18:17,120 --> 00:18:18,760
Kluay, listen to me.

226
00:18:18,840 --> 00:18:22,200
Maybe he's just stressed right now.

227
00:18:22,280 --> 00:18:24,600
Maybe something else is bothering him.

228
00:18:24,680 --> 00:18:26,640
He probably doesn't
want you to stress out too.

229
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:28,640
What else could it be?

230
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:31,880
<i>They're opening the will today, right?</i>

231
00:18:31,960 --> 00:18:34,320
It's probably something big.

232
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:36,720
He must be overthinking.

233
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:38,320
No way.

234
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:42,760
We already talked about that and made
a decision. I don't think it's that.

235
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:46,440
Oh? Then what do you think it is?

236
00:18:48,920 --> 00:18:52,320
Or is he getting annoyed with me?

237
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:54,280
Ugh, Kluay.

238
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:57,400
You're really overthinking this.
It's not like that.

239
00:18:57,480 --> 00:18:59,800
But it feels real, Som.

240
00:18:59,880 --> 00:19:01,120
What should I do?

241
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:04,360
Trust me, it's nothing.

242
00:19:05,880 --> 00:19:08,760
Oh, I have to go, Kluay.

243
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:10,320
The team's here for the meeting.

244
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:12,000
Alright. Go ahead.

245
00:19:12,080 --> 00:19:14,640
Don't overthink, okay? Trust me.

246
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:18,080
Everything's fine.
But if you want to know something,

247
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:19,800
just ask Mr. Warat directly.

248
00:19:19,880 --> 00:19:22,680
Alright. Go ahead. Don't worry about me.

249
00:19:26,680 --> 00:19:27,720
Ugh.

250
00:19:43,280 --> 00:19:44,520
Mr. Warat?

251
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:51,240
Kluay.

252
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:53,800
I have bad news.

253
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:58,200
Don't tell me…

254
00:20:01,960 --> 00:20:02,960
Let's break up.

255
00:20:04,080 --> 00:20:05,240
No, Mr. Warat.

256
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:07,680
Why is this happening?

257
00:20:09,320 --> 00:20:11,000
I've lost my passion for you.

258
00:20:12,720 --> 00:20:15,720
Mr. Warat, how can you say that?

259
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:18,600
I've found a new world.

260
00:20:20,240 --> 00:20:23,640
She makes the whole world look rosy,

261
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:25,400
unlike you.

262
00:20:25,480 --> 00:20:27,600
When did this happen?

263
00:20:27,680 --> 00:20:29,680
We were fine just before this.

264
00:20:29,760 --> 00:20:33,880
There were too many gaps between us.
I couldn't accept it.

265
00:20:35,240 --> 00:20:37,680
Why are you doing this to me?

266
00:20:39,440 --> 00:20:40,440
Kluay.

267
00:20:42,960 --> 00:20:44,360
I've found the mother of my child.

268
00:20:47,760 --> 00:20:49,040
Don't tell me…

269
00:20:50,440 --> 00:20:51,680
it's her.

270
00:20:51,760 --> 00:20:52,920
It's settled, Kluay.

271
00:20:53,960 --> 00:20:55,440
We're going to have a child together.

272
00:20:55,520 --> 00:20:56,880
How is that possible?

273
00:20:57,960 --> 00:20:59,560
What about me?

274
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:02,920
What does she have that I don't?
Is she prettier than me?

275
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:06,120
She's prettier, richer, and hotter.

276
00:21:06,920 --> 00:21:08,320
Let's break up.

277
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:10,320
No, Mr. Warat.

278
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:12,840
Please don't do this to me.

279
00:21:13,360 --> 00:21:16,240
Please don't leave me, Mr. Warat.

280
00:21:16,920 --> 00:21:20,120
Please, I'm begging you.

281
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:22,360
Please don't leave me.

282
00:21:22,440 --> 00:21:24,560
Clinging to me like this

283
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:30,520
won't bring our love back
to what it used to be, Kluay.

284
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:32,200
No…

285
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:34,240
Please, stay with me.

286
00:21:34,320 --> 00:21:37,560
Didn't we promise
we wouldn't leave each other?

287
00:21:38,320 --> 00:21:40,880
I told you already,
I've lost my passion for you.

288
00:21:41,480 --> 00:21:42,560
Kluay,

289
00:21:43,360 --> 00:21:45,080
I'll send you a wedding invitation.

290
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:51,920
<i>Mr. Warat, don't leave me.</i>

291
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:55,320
<i>Mr. Warat!</i>

292
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:58,960
<i>I can't take this. I can't live like this.</i>

293
00:22:07,120 --> 00:22:08,000
Ms. Kluay.

294
00:22:12,840 --> 00:22:14,160
Mr. Arnon?

295
00:22:14,240 --> 00:22:15,720
Are you okay?

296
00:22:18,360 --> 00:22:20,960
Oh, I'm fine.

297
00:22:21,040 --> 00:22:23,800
I was just thinking about something.

298
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:27,120
And…

299
00:22:27,640 --> 00:22:29,440
Mr. Warat?

300
00:22:29,520 --> 00:22:30,640
Oh.

301
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:33,280
Mr. Warat…

302
00:22:40,040 --> 00:22:43,680
Mr. Arnon,
did Mr. Warat tell you anything?

303
00:22:44,520 --> 00:22:45,360
No.

304
00:22:46,880 --> 00:22:49,400
Did anything strange happen?

305
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:53,600
Could it be that
someone sent something to his phone?

306
00:22:55,440 --> 00:22:57,040
What could it be?

307
00:22:59,320 --> 00:23:00,520
Well.

308
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:03,480
And what will happen to today's meeting?

309
00:23:04,240 --> 00:23:05,920
We'll probably have to postpone it.

310
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:08,120
All the relatives have already left.

311
00:23:09,120 --> 00:23:10,800
It's serious.

312
00:23:11,400 --> 00:23:13,200
It must be serious

313
00:23:13,920 --> 00:23:16,280
for him to make that decision.

314
00:23:20,640 --> 00:23:22,320
I don't want anything

315
00:23:23,560 --> 00:23:25,080
that you're giving me.

316
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:26,560
Rat.

317
00:23:28,520 --> 00:23:30,920
Didn't we already agree?

318
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:37,080
I know
you don't want any of my wealth or assets.

319
00:23:37,160 --> 00:23:40,640
But you should also know

320
00:23:40,720 --> 00:23:44,960
that you're the one
who must take over the Vanich business.

321
00:23:45,040 --> 00:23:47,240
It's not just about you.

322
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:51,920
It's not me.

323
00:23:52,520 --> 00:23:54,440
If not you, then who, Warat?

324
00:23:56,720 --> 00:23:58,280
Do you have anything…

325
00:24:00,280 --> 00:24:02,000
that you're still hiding from me?

326
00:24:03,040 --> 00:24:04,080
What do you mean?

327
00:24:10,760 --> 00:24:12,320
I mean the truth.

328
00:24:15,760 --> 00:24:18,600
What are you talking about, Warat?

329
00:24:20,640 --> 00:24:21,680
Grandma,

330
00:24:21,760 --> 00:24:24,400
can you tell me the truth just once?

331
00:24:24,480 --> 00:24:26,560
What truth?

332
00:24:26,640 --> 00:24:28,480
I don't understand.

333
00:24:28,560 --> 00:24:32,680
What exactly are you trying to say, Warat?

334
00:24:42,040 --> 00:24:44,960
Mr. Arnon, should we go in?

335
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:46,960
No.

336
00:24:47,480 --> 00:24:50,360
I think
Mr. Warat should handle this himself.

337
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:55,560
By the way, is the account data ready?

338
00:24:56,960 --> 00:24:59,320
You could say they've been
skimming for a long time.

339
00:24:59,840 --> 00:25:02,600
I've warned Mrs. Wanee many times,

340
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:04,280
but she kept turning a blind eye.

341
00:25:04,360 --> 00:25:08,480
I think that
if Grandma knew but did nothing,

342
00:25:08,560 --> 00:25:12,120
maybe there was something
that forced her to pretend not to see.

343
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:14,960
Is the evidence clear?

344
00:25:16,520 --> 00:25:17,640
Right here.

345
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:21,800
It's full of irregularities.

346
00:25:23,640 --> 00:25:25,440
With evidence this clear,

347
00:25:26,840 --> 00:25:27,920
there's no way they'll get away with it.

348
00:25:36,320 --> 00:25:37,640
This is…

349
00:25:42,080 --> 00:25:43,520
I'm not my father's son.

350
00:25:45,880 --> 00:25:46,920
Warat.

351
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:50,640
It's okay. It's okay.

352
00:25:50,720 --> 00:25:54,080
No matter what anyone says,
it doesn't matter.

353
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:56,480
Nothing is more important than this.

354
00:25:56,560 --> 00:26:00,800
You are my only grandson.

355
00:26:05,120 --> 00:26:06,720
I'm not your grandson.

356
00:26:07,480 --> 00:26:09,840
- My dad…
- That's enough.

357
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:11,720
I don't want to hear it.

358
00:26:11,800 --> 00:26:13,920
And I don't want to know.

359
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:17,480
I don't want to know any more.

360
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:23,200
All I know is that Prae
was my adopted daughter.

361
00:26:23,280 --> 00:26:28,520
So that makes you my only grandson.

362
00:26:28,600 --> 00:26:29,520
Alright?

363
00:26:30,120 --> 00:26:33,920
Grandma,
why have you been hiding this from me?

364
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:36,560
And how could Mr. Sarut be my father?

365
00:26:37,880 --> 00:26:39,600
What really happened?

366
00:26:44,520 --> 00:26:45,920
Please tell me.

367
00:26:47,400 --> 00:26:48,720
I'm begging you.

368
00:26:51,800 --> 00:26:53,880
Can you tell me the truth?

369
00:26:55,760 --> 00:26:57,280
Everything

370
00:26:59,960 --> 00:27:01,640
started from…

371
00:27:07,120 --> 00:27:09,680
Prae, why did you do this?

372
00:27:09,760 --> 00:27:12,440
Are you going to tell me now
who the father of your child is?

373
00:27:12,520 --> 00:27:14,520
Chan, that's enough.

374
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:18,120
Mom, I want to leave this house.

375
00:27:18,200 --> 00:27:19,320
Where will you go?

376
00:27:19,400 --> 00:27:21,160
I don't know.

377
00:27:21,240 --> 00:27:24,160
But if a place doesn't accept me,

378
00:27:24,240 --> 00:27:25,320
I don't want to stay.

379
00:27:26,800 --> 00:27:27,920
You chose this yourself.

380
00:27:28,600 --> 00:27:30,480
Chan, come on.

381
00:27:30,560 --> 00:27:32,880
Mom, don't stop her.

382
00:27:33,600 --> 00:27:35,920
You know how much I love you.

383
00:27:36,640 --> 00:27:40,520
But you also know
I don't feel that way about you.

384
00:27:41,040 --> 00:27:42,240
To me,

385
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:45,360
you're just like a younger sister.

386
00:27:45,440 --> 00:27:47,320
And that's all you'll ever be.

387
00:27:50,120 --> 00:27:52,080
And what's wrong with that?

388
00:27:52,160 --> 00:27:54,080
That way, you can stay
and take care of me forever.

389
00:27:54,160 --> 00:27:55,960
But I have my own life to live.

390
00:27:56,040 --> 00:27:57,600
You've changed

391
00:27:58,120 --> 00:27:59,680
ever since that woman came into your life.

392
00:27:59,760 --> 00:28:02,120
Then you stay. I'll leave.

393
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:03,360
No.

394
00:28:03,880 --> 00:28:06,840
No one is going anywhere.
We'll all stay here together.

395
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:09,400
- Mom. but…
- If you

396
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:12,320
want to be with Ampha,
then you must stay with Prae too.

397
00:28:13,640 --> 00:28:14,480
Mom.

398
00:28:15,080 --> 00:28:18,960
I know you love Ampha.

399
00:28:19,040 --> 00:28:21,440
But I love Prae too.

400
00:28:21,520 --> 00:28:24,880
So no one is going anywhere.

401
00:28:24,960 --> 00:28:27,280
We'll all stay together like this.

402
00:28:34,120 --> 00:28:35,480
<i>And Dad agreed to that?</i>

403
00:28:36,800 --> 00:28:38,000
Rat…

404
00:28:40,520 --> 00:28:42,720
Why are you so selfish?

405
00:28:44,160 --> 00:28:45,640
I know.

406
00:28:46,160 --> 00:28:48,600
I know I'm selfish.

407
00:28:50,480 --> 00:28:52,520
But at this point,

408
00:28:53,120 --> 00:28:58,280
can't you just let everything go?

409
00:29:00,040 --> 00:29:02,200
Do you think it's that easy?

410
00:29:02,720 --> 00:29:06,080
I can't lie to myself like that.

411
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:09,200
It's not about lying. It's just…

412
00:29:09,280 --> 00:29:10,680
Just what?

413
00:29:12,920 --> 00:29:14,200
All this time

414
00:29:15,760 --> 00:29:19,640
we've been together,

415
00:29:21,040 --> 00:29:27,080
have you never once seen me
as your grandmother?

416
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:31,440
That's a different matter.

417
00:29:33,840 --> 00:29:35,000
I understand.

418
00:29:36,800 --> 00:29:39,160
Blood is one thing.

419
00:29:40,880 --> 00:29:42,600
But bonds

420
00:29:43,320 --> 00:29:46,440
and relationships are another.

421
00:29:48,160 --> 00:29:49,920
I raised you,

422
00:29:50,440 --> 00:29:53,880
took care of you since you were little.

423
00:29:56,120 --> 00:29:57,920
Even if now…

424
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:01,680
there's not a single drop

425
00:30:02,800 --> 00:30:05,920
of my blood in you…

426
00:30:08,600 --> 00:30:11,240
just know this.

427
00:30:12,760 --> 00:30:15,760
With every breath I take,

428
00:30:17,720 --> 00:30:19,360
you are my beloved grandson.

429
00:30:20,240 --> 00:30:23,160
My only beloved grandson.

430
00:30:27,080 --> 00:30:29,000
Do you really see me as your grandson?

431
00:30:31,760 --> 00:30:34,960
Then you shouldn't have lied
to the grandson you love.

432
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:44,840
I won't accept

433
00:30:46,080 --> 00:30:48,280
any of your assets.

434
00:30:49,400 --> 00:30:51,600
And you don't have to look for me.

435
00:30:53,120 --> 00:30:55,520
Don't get involved with me anymore.
I'm begging you.

436
00:30:56,440 --> 00:30:57,560
Warat.

437
00:30:58,080 --> 00:31:00,680
Warat. Warat, my dear.

438
00:31:00,760 --> 00:31:03,120
Listen to me, Warat.

439
00:31:57,520 --> 00:32:00,600
Mr. Arnon, I don't think this is good.

440
00:32:00,680 --> 00:32:02,920
Mr. Warat must be
very upset with Mrs. Wanee.

441
00:32:03,440 --> 00:32:05,000
- Uh.
- Hey, don't go.

442
00:32:05,720 --> 00:32:07,000
He'll come back.

443
00:32:08,120 --> 00:32:09,840
But… what if he doesn't?

444
00:32:09,920 --> 00:32:12,440
- Where could he go?
- Uh.

445
00:32:17,280 --> 00:32:18,320
Mr. Warat?

446
00:32:18,840 --> 00:32:20,840
- It's work.
- Oh.

447
00:32:20,920 --> 00:32:23,520
Then I'll go find him.

448
00:32:28,200 --> 00:32:30,640
Hello, Som. I'll come to you.

449
00:32:32,440 --> 00:32:33,760
How is it? Everything done?

450
00:32:33,840 --> 00:32:34,760
Hold the plan for now.

451
00:32:34,840 --> 00:32:35,920
Does Warat know?

452
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:37,240
I don't think so.

453
00:32:37,760 --> 00:32:40,440
But I don't know what he's thinking.

454
00:32:40,520 --> 00:32:42,560
There's billions right in front of him,
yet he walks away like that.

455
00:32:42,640 --> 00:32:46,200
Then it must be something important.

456
00:32:46,720 --> 00:32:47,640
What do you think it is?

457
00:32:47,720 --> 00:32:49,920
It's probably not about the inheritance.

458
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:51,480
I really don't know what he's thinking.

459
00:32:51,560 --> 00:32:56,040
Mr. Sin, my source said Kluay came in
and took all your work documents.

460
00:32:56,120 --> 00:32:58,760
My work documents?
What would she want them for?

461
00:32:58,840 --> 00:33:00,200
I'm not even sure she can read them.

462
00:33:00,280 --> 00:33:02,920
- But…
- Don't worry. She can't do anything to us.

463
00:33:16,200 --> 00:33:17,240
There you are.

464
00:33:20,880 --> 00:33:23,680
So what's wrong with her? Just tell me.

465
00:33:23,760 --> 00:33:26,320
- There's nothing wrong with her at all.
- What?

466
00:33:26,400 --> 00:33:30,000
Physically and mentally,
she's completely normal.

467
00:33:30,080 --> 00:33:33,200
No hallucinations or anything like that?

468
00:33:33,280 --> 00:33:34,160
None.

469
00:33:34,240 --> 00:33:36,800
- Then I'll call Mr. Sin.
- Alright.

470
00:33:41,360 --> 00:33:42,640
Hello, Mr. Sin.

471
00:33:43,280 --> 00:33:44,720
My friend checked everything.

472
00:33:44,800 --> 00:33:46,880
<i>- And?</i>
- Everything's normal.

473
00:33:46,960 --> 00:33:49,440
<i>And what about what I asked you to handle?</i>

474
00:33:50,560 --> 00:33:52,440
It's my friend's aunt.

475
00:33:53,480 --> 00:33:57,080
So what is it this time?
Illegal lottery? Loan sharking?

476
00:33:59,200 --> 00:34:00,280
It's a murder case.

477
00:34:06,440 --> 00:34:07,640
I can't help you with that.

478
00:34:09,239 --> 00:34:10,280
Oh, wait.

479
00:34:10,360 --> 00:34:13,159
Right now, she's only a suspect.

480
00:34:13,239 --> 00:34:14,719
Did she actually do it

481
00:34:15,719 --> 00:34:16,600
or not?

482
00:34:17,960 --> 00:34:18,840
I don't know.

483
00:34:18,920 --> 00:34:21,000
You don't know, so how can I help you?

484
00:34:21,080 --> 00:34:22,920
Please, help me.

485
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:25,360
What can I even do? I'm already out of it.

486
00:34:39,239 --> 00:34:41,920
Everything is all set.
There shouldn't be any problems.

487
00:34:42,639 --> 00:34:44,639
<i>Then go bring Aunt Nong back right away.</i>

488
00:34:45,159 --> 00:34:46,199
Yes.

489
00:35:06,160 --> 00:35:09,640
<i>Grandma, I'm sorry.</i>

490
00:35:10,760 --> 00:35:12,800
<i>What are you apologizing for, Ameena?</i>

491
00:35:13,680 --> 00:35:16,560
<i>I'm pregnant with Warat's child.</i>

492
00:35:16,640 --> 00:35:19,680
<i>Pregnant?</i>
<i>You're pregnant with Rat's child?</i>

493
00:35:19,760 --> 00:35:20,960
<i>Yes.</i>

494
00:35:21,480 --> 00:35:24,200
<i>Grandma, but I…</i>

495
00:35:25,480 --> 00:35:27,040
<i>Rat?</i>

496
00:35:27,560 --> 00:35:29,600
<i>How could he do something like this?</i>

497
00:35:30,120 --> 00:35:35,040
<i>But I know</i>
<i>he's in a relationship with Kluay.</i>

498
00:35:35,120 --> 00:35:36,320
<i>I don't want to…</i>

499
00:35:36,400 --> 00:35:40,280
<i>You don't need to say anything more.</i>
<i>I'll handle it.</i>

500
00:35:57,800 --> 00:35:59,000
How was your stay there, Aunt Nong?

501
00:36:00,560 --> 00:36:01,600
Sin.

502
00:36:04,400 --> 00:36:05,960
Why did you send me there?

503
00:36:07,080 --> 00:36:08,840
Uh… has Chatchai gone back already?

504
00:36:11,840 --> 00:36:14,720
Yes, he left right after dropping me off.

505
00:36:16,240 --> 00:36:19,480
Auntie,
I've taken care of the police matter.

506
00:36:24,880 --> 00:36:26,120
Just tell me.

507
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:28,880
What are you trying to do?

508
00:36:29,760 --> 00:36:30,960
Sin…

509
00:36:36,200 --> 00:36:37,920
I feel sorry for you.

510
00:36:41,040 --> 00:36:42,520
Why would you feel sorry for me?

511
00:36:45,880 --> 00:36:47,480
Back then, you were still young.

512
00:36:49,080 --> 00:36:50,800
You probably don't remember

513
00:36:52,600 --> 00:36:54,040
what happened.

514
00:36:58,920 --> 00:37:02,760
<i>After Mr. Jinchai married Na,</i>

515
00:37:02,840 --> 00:37:05,000
<i>your family</i>

516
00:37:05,080 --> 00:37:08,160
<i>looked like</i>
<i>a perfect dream to many people.</i>

517
00:37:09,960 --> 00:37:13,880
<i>At that time, Na looked very happy.</i>

518
00:37:14,800 --> 00:37:17,480
<i>Mr. Jinchai was a capable man,</i>

519
00:37:17,560 --> 00:37:21,200
<i>and Na took good care of the household.</i>

520
00:37:25,240 --> 00:37:26,560
<i>But then one day,</i>

521
00:37:27,920 --> 00:37:29,920
<i>that woman came into their lives</i>

522
00:37:31,920 --> 00:37:34,160
<i>and ruined everything.</i>

523
00:37:35,280 --> 00:37:36,760
<i>Since then,</i>

524
00:37:37,320 --> 00:37:40,320
<i>I've never seen Na smile again.</i>

525
00:37:50,240 --> 00:37:51,360
NEXT EPISODE

526
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:52,840
<i>Ameena came and said</i>

527
00:37:54,640 --> 00:37:56,920
Mr. Warat got her pregnant.

528
00:37:59,040 --> 00:38:03,280
<i>I'm so afraid, Boonsita,</i>
<i>that Warat will disappear</i>

529
00:38:04,200 --> 00:38:06,000
and never come back again.

530
00:38:07,120 --> 00:38:11,120
Grandma,
I'll be the one to bring Warat back.

531
00:38:12,520 --> 00:38:14,440
<i>If we want our plan,</i>

532
00:38:14,520 --> 00:38:17,680
to be complete,
we'll have to get rid of Kluay too.

533
00:38:17,760 --> 00:38:20,160
What does she have to do with anything?

534
00:38:21,280 --> 00:38:23,720
Mrs. Wanee announced the will.

535
00:38:25,720 --> 00:38:27,840
Even without Mr. Warat?

536
00:38:28,880 --> 00:38:31,280
MRS. WANEE VANICH

537
00:40:52,840 --> 00:40:54,960
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
